            <h2>
                For Buyers: An Easy Way to Save <span class="italics">Thousands</span> While Buying a Home
            </h2>
            <p>
                Buying a home is maybe the biggest purchase of your life.  You <span class="italics">don't</span> want to spend any more money than you have to.  But if you buy a home that has hidden defects or deficiencies, you are doing just that.  Some have estimated that <a href="https://www.realtor.com/news/trends/how-much-new-homeowners-spend-after-moving-in/" target="_blank">home buyers spend over $10,000 in the first year</a> after move-in, including thousands in home repairs and maintenance.
            </p>
            <p>
                Knowing what you’re <span class="italics">really</span> buying (a great house + certain repairs and maintenance costs in that new house) will help you make budget-smart decisions and prepare for your family’s financial future.
            </p>
            <p>
                Cornerstone Home Inspections allows you to “test drive” your new house by examining it top to bottom and then walking through it with you.  We are specially trained to look at the components of each home system and then evaluate their condition so that you know what you’re buying into when you’re moving into your new home.
            </p>
        </div>
        <div class="tab-pane container fade" id="agent">
            <div class="d-flex flex-column">
                <h2>
                    For Realtors: The Secret to Selling Homes <span class="italics">Fast</span>
                </h2>
                <p>
                    Did you know that the number of buyers who back away from a deal is increasing more and more each year and that first-time home buyers are the most likely to back out before closing?
                </p>
                <p>
                    That can be frightening, especially considering that the percentage of first-time home buyers is increasing rapidly.  To combat this pandemic of cold feet, <a href="http://articles.latimes.com/2007/aug/26/realestate/re-inspect26" target="_blank">media outlets like the <span class="italics">Los Angeles Times</span></a> are suggesting a new kind of selling strategy: pre-listing inspections.
                </p>
                <p class="m-0">
                    Cornerstone Home Inspections can help protect you from time wasted on lost deals by providing your clients with a home inspection <span class="italics">before</span> you list the home on the market.  We provide you with a shareable electronic inspection report and a “Move-in Certified” seal to put on your marketing materials so that potential buyers know their new home is safe and priced correctly.
                </p>
                <img src="~/Images/moveincertified.gif" alt="Move-in Certified logo" class="align-self-center m-2" />
                <p>
                    The fact is, your buyers are eventually going to conduct an inspection. You may as well know what they are going to find by getting there first.  And having an inspection performed ahead of time helps in many other ways, such as:
                </p>
                <ul>
                    <li>It allows you to see your home through the eyes of a critical and neutral third party.</li>
                    <li>It alerts you to immediate safety issues before agents and visitors tour your home.</li>
                    <li>It may alert you to items of immediate concern, such as radon gas or active termite infestation.</li>
                </ul>
                <p>
                    It also permits you to make repairs ahead of time so that ...
                </p>
                <ul>
                    <li><strong>Defects won't become negotiating stumbling blocks later.</strong></li>
                    <li>There is no delay in obtaining the Use and Occupancy Permit.</li>
                    <li>You have the time to get reasonably priced contractors or make the repairs yourself, if qualified.</li>
                    <li>It helps you to price your home realistically.</li>
                    <li>It may relieve prospects' concerns and suspicions.</li>
                    <li><strong>It may encourage the buyer to waive his inspection contingency.</strong></li>
                    <li>It reduces your liability by adding professional supporting documentation to your disclosure statement.</li>
                </ul>
                <p>
                    For more information about the Move-in Certified program, go to <a href="https://www.moveincertified.com/" target="_blank">www.moveincertified.com</a> or call us at <a href="tel:+13853093164">385-309-3164</a>.
                </p>
            </div>
