<!--FAQS-->
<div class="container faqs-container" id="faqs">
    <h3>FAQ's</h3>
    <button type="button" class="btn btn-info" onclick="reveal_faqA(1)">What is a home inspection?</button>
    <div class="card bg-light faq-panel" id="faq-1-a">
        <div class="card-body">
            A home inspection is a non-invasive, visual inspection of important systems and components in your home. Home inspections help buyers <a href="#info-container" class="scrolly-50">find the right house for the right price</a> by helping you identify problems that could pose a safety hazard or negatively affect the value of your home.
        </div>
    </div>
    <button type="button" class="btn btn-info" onclick="reveal_faqA(2)">What is included in a home inspection?</button>
    <div class="card bg-light faq-panel" id="faq-2-a">
        <div class="card-body">
            At Cornerstone, we strive to provide you with the most thorough inspection available, following InterNACHI's Standards of Practice. This includes a detailed report of the roof, exterior, interior, foundation, attic, insulations, basement, HVAC, plumbing, electrical, doors, and windows as well as any attached garages or decks. If you have questions about what we cover, call or text us at <a href="tel:+13853093164">385-309-3164</a>. For more information about InterNACHI's Standards of Practice, go to <a href="https://www.nachi.org/sop" target="_blank">nachi.org/sop</a>.
        </div>
    </div>
    <button type="button" class="btn btn-info" onclick="reveal_faqA(3)" style="display: none">Why should I want a home inspection?</button>
    <div class="card bg-light faq-panel" id="faq-3-a">
        <div class="card-body">

        </div>
    </div>
    <button type="button" class="btn btn-info" onclick="reveal_faqA(4)">What should I look for in a home inspector?</button>
    <div class="card bg-light faq-panel" id="faq-4-a">
        <div class="card-body">
            Hiring a bad home inspector can be as bad as not hiring one at all.  Home inspectors should always be certified and trained by an inspection certification association, and they should have your best interest at heart.  At Cornerstone, our inspectors are always certified with the International Association of Certified Home Inspectors (InterNACHI).  This means that we’re held to the highest standards of quality in the industry and are required to pass a rigorous inspection exam and perform several home inspections prior to certification. It also means that we follow InterNACHI’s Standards of Practice and Code of Ethics, which is why Cornerstone Inspectors will <span class="italics">never</span> suggest a service you don’t need.  We provide each client with an inspection report in hard copy and online through state-of-the-art inspection software, and we will stay in communication with you long after the inspection is complete to answer questions about this report and help you maintain your home.
        </div>
    </div>
    <button type="button" class="btn btn-info" onclick="reveal_faqA(5)">How long does an inspection usually take?</button>
    <div class="card bg-light faq-panel" id="faq-5-a">
        <div class="card-body">
            Times vary depending on a variety of factors,
            but plan on your inspector spending about 3-4 hours.
        </div>
    </div>
    <button type="button" class="btn btn-info" onclick="reveal_faqA(6)">Should I be there for the inspection?</button>
    <div class="card bg-light faq-panel" id="faq-6-a">
        <div class="card-body">
            Most home buyers find it valuable to arrive about 1 hour before the inspection
            is complete and walk through the home with the inspector.
        </div>
    </div>
    <button type="button" class="btn btn-info" style="display: none" onclick="reveal_faqA(7)">What sets Cornerstone Home Inspections apart from other inspection companies?</button>
    <div class="card bg-light faq-panel" id="faq-7-a">
        <div class="card-body">
            Each of our inspectors is certified with InterNACHI, the largest association
            of real estate inspectors in the world.  We are meticulous and dedicated in
            our reports, and each inspection report is delivered to you
            in hard copy and online through state-of-the-art inspection software.
            Friendly and accessible, we will stay in communication
            with you long after the inspection is complete to answer questions, improve our
            service, and help you maintain your home.
        </div>
    </div>
